    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">C(3) + H(4) base value</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>C is worth 3 points and H is worth 4 — together they contribute 7 points before any premium squares. This makes CH words inherently higher-scoring than most digraphs, and placing them across Double or Triple Letter squares amplifies the value dramatically.</p>

